The architecture combines:

Dual-stream MMDiT blocks (16 layers) for multimodal processing
Single-stream DiT blocks (32 layers) for global consistency
Mixture of Experts (MoE) in the FFN sub-networks for efficiency

2. Dynamic Routing for Efficiency
Both dual-stream and single-stream DiT architecture are remoulded with dynamic Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) design that aims to dynamically route data through specialized expert modules based on input characteristics. HiDream - Draw Things WIKI
This sparse architecture achieves:

Computational efficiency without sacrificing quality
Dynamic resource allocation based on scene complexity
Better handling of details like edges, colors, and lighting

